[thinking] **Evaluating dependencies setup**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how to represent dependencies with deterministic_setup entries, which drivers can apply before generation. I think plexus-testing is the easiest way to set up dependency injection (DI), but I wonder if that implies the library requires extra setup. 
[thinking] 
[thinking] I notice that the upstream test utilizes both @PlexusTest and POM test dependencies, along with instances where fields are injected. Without the container, full rendering APIs might be null, so meaningful coverage should use the container. I'll check if `org.eclipse.sisu.plexus` includes the necessary dependencies.
[thinking] 
